reviews.text: Awesome-Excellent Experience.Nestled away in a very quiet park of Hong Kong Park is this little gem. This was the most formal of the tea traditions I experienced in Hong Kong and every place does things a bit different. The food here was pretty good, mostly dim sum. The staff were 100% totally serious & committed to the entire experience making the ambiance all that much better and it was already quite beautiful and spotlessly clean.Workers with precise movements and timing took their job as serious as heart attacks and further added to ambiance. Has a nice garden view of park's peaceful greenery, nothing dramatic, but a very welcome sight in Hong Kong.Beautiful inside and out.

Seren atmosphere. Courteous floor Staff.

Each tea type on the menu explained, very warm experience.

Jasmine pearl tea was very soothing, particularly recommended by the staff for a rainy summer evening
Lovely vegetarian dim sum. Hard to find hence it's great to be able to enjoy the variety and quality of such food
Great ambiance, very friendly staff.  Large variety of tea to choose from.  It's a great place to go with a book, have some tea and vegetarian dim sum to spend an afternoon in slow pace.
Good vegetarian dim sum, though the atmosphere and tea is the main reason you should be visiting here. The walk through the park to get here, especially in a morning, is great.

reviews.text: Great place for tea and dim sum! We mainly came here for their great selection of vegetarian dim sum options and weren't disappointed! Absolutely loved the steamed vegetable dumplings! Although a bit pricey it's definitely worth a visit.

Good place to spend an afternoon to enjoy some good Chinese tea and vegetarian dim sum. The dim sums were lighter than the usual ones but still beautifully made with clean flavours. I especially love their wasabi-flavoured green pea cakes.

Knowledgeable staff at the tea shop. 
Willing to brew tasting samples to assist in your selection. 
Good quality tea.
Some of the best tea in the city.

If you love Chinese tea, or just want to get a taste of local heritage, this is the place for you! I love Chinese tea myself, and I had a fine time here. They have any type of tea you can imagine, and even some I have practically never heard of! If you don't like Chinese tea, still try out the cold brewed tea, which is not as heavy.

哈哈。说实在的。我本来就是个习惯给五颗星的。评价给的越多，就越在意星颗给的太多还是太少啦。这么说来，我的评价好像就不太有用了哦-.- 但还是要写，就因为爽！这是朋友带领的。恰好这朋友也在航海，抵达了香港的港湾。那天来时，茶站里人倒是不多。但我们穿过了CBD里规模庞大的购物中心，再到了公园搜寻这茶站。回想起来，有点像走过不同地方的感觉。这是香港藏着的magical体验吧。茶类丰富。有点浪费在我这身上。
